<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12810&amp;p=147838#p147838"><![CDATA[
If you want DS features, make a PC game or move out of the UK and Japan. Here in the States, we have a Supreme Court that ruled in <em>Lexmark v. Static Control Components</em> to limit how successful a &quot;circumvents the security measures&quot; legal theory can be when &quot;the security measures&quot; exist primarily for the purpose of subjecting complementary goods to vendor lock-in. For a while, the major electronics chain Best Buy was selling Datel's Games 'n Music, a DS flash cart that can run only homebrew.<br /><br />Neither GBA nor GBC is more than 20 years old.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue May 19, 2015 7:33 pm</p><hr />
